cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper discusses methods for learning word representations using large text corpora, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a joint learning method that incorporates semantic lexicons, which involves machine learning techniques and could fall under sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which could relate to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
